{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877624674,"sessionID":"ses_285744ec3ffeuFGw0VUiOZSttc","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8c8758001KPyd3TFGTwOQkL","messageID":"msg_d7a8c6e60001YuhiAGsw877Kfu","sessionID":"ses_285744ec3ffeuFGw0VUiOZSttc","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_c704ed73d748477bb987bcb1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md","content":"# AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端 Tasks\n\n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Package Structure & Utilities ✓\n\n- [x] **T1.1** Create `agentcube/__init__.py`\n  - Import `CodeInterpreterClient` from `code_interpreter`\n  - Import `AgentRuntimeClient` from `agent_runtime`\n  - Define `__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py`\n  - Verify: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient` works\n\n- [x] **T1.2** Create `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n  - Define `AgentCubeError(Exception)` base class\n  - Define `CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError)` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command` attributes\n  - Define `SessionError(AgentCubeError)` placeholder for future expansion\n  - Define `DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError)` placeholder for future expansion\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/exceptions.py`\n  - Verify: All exception classes instantiate correctly\n\n- [x] **T1.3** Create `agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n  - Empty file (module marker)\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n  - Verify: Module imports successfully\n\n- [x] **T1.4** Create `agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Import `requests`, `HTTPAdapter`, `Retry`\n  - Implement `create_session(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10, max_retries=0)`\n  - Configure retry strategy with `backoff_factor=0.1`, `status_forcelist=[429, 500, 502, 503, 504]`\n  - Mount `HTTPAdapter` for `http://` and `https://`\n  - Return configured `requests.Session`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verify: Session has adapters mounted for http/https with correct pool sizes\n\n- [x] **T1.5** Create `agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n  - Implement `read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str`\n  - Return file contents stripped\n  - Return `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n  - Verify: Returns empty string for missing file, stripped content for existing\n\n- [x] **T1.6** Create `agentcube/utils/log.py`\n  - Implement `get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO)`\n  - Create logger with stream handler\n  - Format: `%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s`\n  - Avoid duplicate handlers\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/log.py`\n  - Verify: Logger outputs formatted messages\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Control Plane Client ✓\n\n- [x] **T2.1** Create `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n  - Import all three client classes: `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n  - Define `__all__` with client names\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n  - Verify: Clients importable from `agentcube.clients`\n\n- [x] **T2.2** Create `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n  - Import `ControlPlaneClient`, `os`, `requests`, utilities\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Module structure correct\n\n- [x] **T2.3** Implement `ControlPlaneClient.__init__()`\n  - Parameters: `workload_manager_url`, `auth_token`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n  - Resolve `base_url` from arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env\n  - Raise `ValueError` if URL missing\n  - Resolve auth token from arg or service account file\n  - Create session with `create_session()`\n  - Set headers: `Content-Type`, optional `Authorization`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Instantiates with URL, uses env fallback, handles missing token gracefully\n\n- [x] **T2.4** Implement `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()`\n  - Parameters: `name=\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `metadata=None`, `ttl=3600`\n  - POST to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter`\n  - JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata`\n  - Timeout: `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n  - Return `response.json()[\"sessionId\"]`\n  - Raise `ValueError` if `sessionId` missing\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Returns session ID from mock response\n\n- [x] **T2.5** Implement `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()`\n  - Parameter: `session_id: str`\n  - DELETE to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n  - Return `True` on success or 404\n  - Return `False` on other errors (log warning)\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Idempotent on 404, logs on error\n\n- [x] **T2.6** Implement `ControlPlaneClient.close()`\n  - Call `self.session.close()`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n  - Verify: HTTP session closed\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Data Plane Clients ✓\n\n- [x] **T3.1** Create `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n  - Import `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, dependencies\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Module structure correct\n\n- [x] **T3.2** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.__init__()`\n  - Parameters: `session_id`, `router_url`, `namespace`, `cr_name`, `base_url`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n  - Resolve `base_url`: use provided OR compute from `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name`\n  - Raise `ValueError` if can't resolve\n  - Create session, set `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Base URL computed correctly, session header set\n\n- [x] **T3.3** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient._request()`\n  - Parameters: `method`, `endpoint`, `body=None`, `**kwargs`\n  - Build URL with `urljoin(self.base_url, endpoint)`\n  - Set `Content-Type: application/json` if body present\n  - Apply timeout from kwargs or defaults\n  - Return `requests.Response`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Request sent with correct headers and timeout\n\n- [x] **T3.4** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command()`\n  - Parameters: `command: Union[str, List[str]]`, `timeout: Optional[float]`\n  - Convert string command to list\n  - Build JSON body: `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}`\n  - Apply read timeout buffer: `timeout_value + 2.0`\n  - POST to `api/execute`\n  - Raise `CommandExecutionError` if `exit_code != 0`\n  - Return `stdout` string\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Returns stdout, raises on non-zero exit\n\n- [x] **T3.5** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.run_code()`\n  - Parameters: `language: str`, `code: str`, `timeout: Optional[float]`\n  - Support `python`, `py`, `python3`\n  - Write timestamped `.py` file via `write_file()`\n  - Execute via `python3 <file>` using `execute_command()`\n  - Raise `ValueError` for unsupported languages\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Python code executes correctly\n\n- [x] **T3.6** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.write_file()`\n  - Parameters: `content: str`, `remote_path: str`\n  - Base64 encode content\n  - POST JSON to `api/files`: `path`, `content`, `mode=\"0644\"`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: File created via base64 encoding\n\n- [x] **T3.7** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.upload_file()`\n  - Parameters: `local_path: str`, `remote_path: str`\n  - Read local file as binary\n  - POST multipart to `api/files` with `file`, `path`, `mode`\n  - Set `x-agentcube-session-id` header explicitly\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Multipart upload succeeds\n\n- [x] **T3.8** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.download_file()`\n  - Parameters: `remote_path: str`, `local_path: str`\n  - Clean path: `remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n  - GET from `api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True`\n  - Write chunks to local file\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: File downloaded correctly\n\n- [x] **T3.9** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.list_files()`\n  - Parameter: `path: str = \".\"`\n  - GET from `api/files` with query `path`\n  - Return JSON response\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Returns file list\n\n- [x] **T3.10** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.close()`\n  - Call `self.session.close()`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: HTTP session closed\n\n- [x] **T3.11** Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - Import `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`, dependencies\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Module structure correct\n\n- [x] **T3.12** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.__init__()`\n  - Parameters: `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n  - Compute `base_url` from `router_url` + namespace + agent_name path using `urljoin()`\n  - Create session with `create_session()`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Base URL computed correctly, connection pool configured (10/10)\n\n- [x] **T3.13** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()`\n  - GET from `self.base_url`\n  - Read `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n  - Raise `ValueError` if header missing\n  - Return session ID\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Extracts session ID from response header\n\n- [x] **T3.14** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke()`\n  - Parameters: `session_id`, `payload: Dict[str, Any]`, `timeout: Optional[float]`\n  - Set headers: `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json`\n  - Apply timeout: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` or instance default\n  - POST JSON payload to `self.base_url`\n  - Return `requests.Response`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Request sent with correct headers and timeout\n\n- [x] **T3.15** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.close()`\n  - Call `self.session.close()`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: HTTP session closed\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: Configuration & Environment Handling ✓\n\n- [x] **T4.1** Implement environment variable resolution for `ROUTER_URL`\n  - Check explicit parameter first\n  - Fall back to `os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")`\n  - Raise `ValueError` if both missing\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`, `code_interpreter.py`\n  - Verify: Env var fallback works, clear error on missing\n\n- [x] **T4.2** Implement environment variable resolution for `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`\n  - Check explicit parameter first\n  - Fall back to `os.getenv(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")`\n  - Raise `ValueError` if both missing\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Env var fallback works, clear error on missing\n\n- [x] **T4.3** Implement timeout defaults\n  - Default `timeout=120` (read timeout)\n  - Default `connect_timeout=5.0`\n  - Use tuple form `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)` for requests\n  - File: All client `__init__` methods\n  - Verify: Timeouts applied correctly to HTTP requests\n\n- [x] **T4.4** Implement per-call timeout override\n  - Allow `timeout` parameter on `invoke()`, `execute_command()` methods\n  - Override instance default for that call only\n  - File: Data plane client methods\n  - Verify: Timeout override works per call\n\n- [x] **T4.5** Implement connection pool configuration\n  - Default `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n  - Pass to `create_session()` for all clients\n  - File: All client `__init__` methods\n  - Verify: Connection pools configured with 10/10\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: Error Handling ✓\n\n- [x] **T5.1** Implement `ValueError` for missing URLs\n  - Check in `__init__` after resolving from env\n  - Message: `\"router_url must be provided or ROUTER_URL environment variable must be set\"`\n  - File: `agent_runtime.py`, `code_interpreter.py`, `control_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Clear error message on missing URL\n\n- [x] **T5.2** Implement `ValueError` for missing session header\n  - Check response header after bootstrap GET\n  - Message: `\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n  - File: `agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Raised when header missing\n\n- [x] **T5.3** Implement `ValueError` for uninitialized session\n  - Check `session_id` before `invoke()`\n  - Message: `\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"`\n  - File: `agent_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Raised when invoke called without session\n\n- [x] **T5.4** Implement `CommandExecutionError` for non-zero exit\n  - Check `exit_code` after command execution\n  - Include `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command` in exception\n  - File: `code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Raised with correct attributes on non-zero exit\n\n- [x] **T5.5** Handle 404 as idempotent success\n  - Return `True` on 404 in `delete_session()`\n  - Log warning for other error codes\n  - File: `control_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Delete is idempotent\n\n- [x] **T5.6** Propagate HTTP errors\n  - Call `response.raise_for_status()` after requests\n  - Allow `requests.HTTPError` and `requests.RequestException` to propagate\n  - File: All data plane methods\n  - Verify: HTTP errors raised to caller\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: High-Level Client Integration ✓\n\n- [x] **T6.1** Create `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n  - Import `CodeInterpreterClient`, dependencies\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n  - Verify: Module structure correct\n\n- [x] **T6.2** Implement `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__()`\n  - Parameters: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `auth_token`, `verbose`, `session_id`\n  - Create `ControlPlaneClient`\n  - Create session via `cp_client.create_session()` if `session_id` not provided\n  - Call `_init_data_plane()` with cleanup on failure\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n  - Verify: Client instantiates, session created or reused\n\n- [x] **T6.3** Implement `CodeInterpreterClient._init_data_plane()`\n  - Create `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with session_id, router_url, namespace, name\n  - Store as `self.dp_client`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n  - Verify: Data plane client initialized\n\n- [x] **T6.4** Implement `CodeInterpreterClient.__enter__()` and `__exit__()`\n  - `__enter__`: return `self`\n  - `__exit__`: call `self.stop()`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n  - Verify: Context manager protocol works\n\n- [x] **T6.5** Implement `CodeInterpreterClient.stop()`\n  - Close data plane client\n  - Delete session via `cp_client.delete_session()`\n  - Close control plane client\n  - Log cleanup actions\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n  - Verify: All resources cleaned up\n\n- [x] **T6.6** Implement delegation methods\n  - `execute_command(command, timeout)` → `dp_client.execute_command()`\n  - `run_code(language, code, timeout)` → `dp_client.run_code()`\n  - `write_file(content, remote_path)` → `dp_client.write_file()`\n  - `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` → `dp_client.upload_file()`\n  - `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` → `dp_client.download_file()`\n  - `list_files(path)` → `dp_client.list_files()`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n  - Verify: All methods delegate correctly\n\n- [x] **T6.7** Create `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - Import `AgentRuntimeClient`, dependencies\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Module structure correct\n\n- [x] **T6.8** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__()`\n  - Parameters: `agent_name`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n  - Store instance attributes\n  - Initialize logger with verbose level\n  - Resolve `router_url` from arg or `ROUTER_URL` env\n  - Create `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n  - Bootstrap session ID if not provided\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Client instantiates, session bootstrapped\n\n- [x] **T6.9** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.__enter__()` and `__exit__()`\n  - `__enter__`: return `self`\n  - `__exit__`: call `self.close()`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Context manager protocol works\n\n- [x] **T6.10** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()`\n  - Parameter: `payload: Dict[str, Any]`, `timeout: Optional[float]`\n  - Check `session_id` is set, raise `ValueError` if not\n  - Call `dp_client.invoke()` with session_id, payload, timeout\n  - Return `response.json()`\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Invocation returns JSON response\n\n- [x] **T6.11** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.close()`\n  - Close data plane client\n  - Log cleanup\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - Verify: Resources cleaned up\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7: Session ID Management ✓\n\n- [x] **T7.1** Implement session header constant\n  - Define `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"` (lowercase)\n  - Use constant consistently across clients\n  - File: `agent_runtime_data_plane.py`, `code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Header name consistent\n\n- [x] **T7.2** Implement session ID bootstrapping\n  - GET invocation endpoint to obtain session ID from response header\n  - Store session ID in client instance\n  - File: `agent_runtime.py`, `agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Session ID obtained from Router\n\n- [x] **T7.3** Implement session ID header setting\n  - Set `x-agentcube-session-id` in session headers after bootstrap\n  - Include header in all data plane requests\n  - File: `agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: Header sent with all requests\n\n- [x] **T7.4** Implement explicit session ID support\n  - Allow `session_id` parameter in high-level clients\n  - Skip bootstrap when session_id provided\n  - File: `agent_runtime.py`, `code_interpreter.py`\n  - Verify: Reuses existing session when provided\n\n---\n\n## Phase 8: URL Path Building ✓\n\n- [x] **T8.1** Implement Router URL path building\n  - Use `urljoin()` for relative path拼接\n  - Path format: `/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n  - File: `agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: URL computed correctly\n\n- [x] **T8.2** Implement Workload Manager URL path building\n  - Path format: `/v1/code-interpreter` for create\n  - Path format: `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` for delete\n  - File: `control_plane.py`\n  - Verify: URLs computed correctly\n\n- [x] **T8.3** Implement Code Interpreter data plane URL building\n  - Support `api/execute`, `api/files`, `api/files/{path}`\n  - Use `urljoin()` for relative paths\n  - File: `code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n  - Verify: URLs computed correctly\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. ✅ All HTTP endpoints follow spec-defined paths and parameters\n2. ✅ Connection pool correctly configured (10/10)\n3. ✅ Timeout behavior as expected (default 120s read / 5.0s connect)\n4. ✅ Exception hierarchy complete (`AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, placeholders)\n5. ✅ Environment variable resolution works (`ROUTER_URL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`)\n6. ✅ Unit tests cover all scenarios (HTTP timeout, pool reuse, error cases)\n7. ✅ Session header uses lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`\n8. ✅ Read timeout buffer (+2.0s) applied to command execution\n9. ✅ Control plane handles 404 as idempotent success on delete\n10. ✅ Data plane init failure triggers cleanup and re-raise\n11. ✅ Router URL validation: `ValueError` if both arg and env missing\n12. ✅ Bootstrap session ID from Router invocation endpoint\n13. ✅ Per-call timeout override supported\n14. ✅ `urljoin()` used for relative path building\n15. ✅ All clients implement context manager protocol\n16. ✅ Logging configured with verbose option\n17. ✅ Package exports: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient`\n18. ✅ Clients export: `from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient, ...`\n\n---\n\n**Notes:**\n- Stage ST-3 marked complete: all HTTP clients and infrastructure implemented\n- Session header naming: uses lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` throughout\n- Timeout handling: read timeout gets +2.0s buffer for command execution to avoid premature `ReadTimeout`\n- Exception usage: `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` defined but not raised by core clients (reserved for future expansion)\n- Distributed configuration: no single `Configuration` class; each client resolves own settings from args/env\n- Connection pooling: all clients use `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` by default\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1